<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Lind on 05-28-2002 02:33 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[b]Giving druids a complete heal would not make it harder for clerics to get groups IF they give us the things I am talking about. The problem with clerics in EXP groups is we add nothing to damage output. If they increase that, and give druids a complete heal then both classes profit greatly. By also giving us these abilites we could then have the option of soloing if we couldn't find a group.[/b]
 
  Thinking druids contribute to the damage output of a group (or wizards) is false.  Specced in evocation with full AA and FT using moonfire (1150 for 320 before spec) on low resist mobs a druid or wizard will not even come close to keeping up with the damage of a comperable meleer without a lot of time to med between each fight.  Duoing with a primal monk I do 1/2 to 1/3 the damage they do.  Druids and wizards are complete, total and utter XP sinks in a group.  And the fact is with Judgement's 2.85 damage to mana clerics aren't THAT far off druid's nukeability (and outnuke druids until 57's frost.)

[b]Give druids complete heal, give clerics undead abilities, some better damage output and better defensive skills. everyone wins.[/b]
 
  All non melee classes need better defence.  A 1400AC druid will get bent over and raped hard by a low blue mob a monk with 1200AC wouldn't even notice was there.
 
  Clerics need MUCH better undead capability.
 
  Druids would probably put CH to use but at 60 VI has pretty much said druids are wizards and have been treating them like wizards for the most part it seems.  I think the zillion clerics for a raid and clogging up the /LFGers at the zoneline is here to stay.  I think those hoping for druid healing will be lucky to see "balancing" mean druids can keep up with rampage damage, and clerics left just as they are because "they're perfect" *gag*</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
